The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, March 02, 2004 				 Cow arrest
																								Raisen, March 1 (PTI): Nearly a month after cow slaughter was banned in Madhya Pradesh, one person was arrested here for killing a cow which had entered his fields for grazing.																								Nasir Khan was arrested following a complaint by the cows owner Govardhan Yadav, who alleged that his cow died after it was hit with a baton and stoned by Nasir when it entered his field, sub-divisional magistrate S.C. Sharma said today.																								The accused said in his statement that he was trying to drive away the cow from his fields when a stone hit the beasts head accidentally, causing its death. 																								He claimed he had no intention of killing the animal.																								Soon after the incident, members of both communities discussed the matter among themselves and took immediate steps to prevent any untoward incident and to stop anti-social elements from taking advantage.
